::Q1 (Easy)::What are catalog items in the context of Ataccama ONE? {
    =A) Actual data that you plan to analyze, structured into attributes.
    ~B) Database tables and attributes as columns in a table.
    ~C) Data sources and their metadata.
    ~D) Business terms and their definitions.
    ####[Global Feedback] Catalog items represent the actual data that you plan to analyze, and they are structured into attributes.
    [Source\: Catalog Items \:\: Ataccama ONE]
}

::Q2 (Easy)::What is the purpose of the Data Catalog section in Ataccama ONE? {
    ~A) To manage data sources and their metadata.
    =B) To view and manage catalog items, including their attributes and rules.
    ~C) To run data quality evaluation and profiling.
    ~D) To create data stories and visualizations.
    ####[Global Feedback] The Data Catalog section is where you can find and manage catalog items, including their attributes, added rules, and terms.
    [Source\: Catalog Items \:\: Ataccama ONE]
}

::Q3 (Easy)::How can you view the results of data quality evaluation in Ataccama ONE? {
    =A) By navigating to the catalog item or attribute and switching to the Data Quality tab.
    ~B) By running a data quality evaluation report.
    ~C) By viewing the data quality results in the Data Catalog section.
    ~D) By using the Data Quality API.
    ####[Global Feedback] To view the results of data quality evaluation, navigate to the catalog item or attribute and switch to the Data Quality tab.
    [Source\: View results of DQ evaluation]
}
